      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;klona wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;Let me muddy the waters a bit for ya ... Lol&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you root/rot a ton and love to solo, go with Alt.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you nuke a ton and love to group as DPS go with Alt.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you love to be the main healer go with Alt.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Why is Alt the best choice?  Focus gear.  Get Affliction Haste and Burning Affliction and Affliction Efficientcy for Root/Rot.  Then get Improved Damage for nuking.  You should already have Spell Haste and Mana Pres.  Improved Healing, Improved Healing, and Extended Enhancement and you are done.  Usually i have to move my gear around a lot to get the use out of some of these based on what I am doing at the time. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Alteration is the one spell you are most likely to cast more then any other draining the most mana.  You will use it on yourself, others, and group members.  Clerics are the best at healing, but do not ever discount a druid's ability to heal.  Buffs and DPS are our greatest attribute in groups however.  Just remember that you will even use ALT when you root/rot cause grasping root and those above it are all ALT based.  Ports, snares, heals, roots, evacs, a bunch of your buffs (regen) are all ALT.  You will get your money's worth EVEN if you solo all the way 70.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;BTW:  I have yet to see specialization be the defining factor in any of my classes careers.  Yes it does help from time to time but would never depend on it in a fight.  Most toons think it does more then a &amp;quot;chance&amp;quot; of reducing mana usage on spells even at max levels it is not that much mana compared to a life and death situation.  This is a long term decision and one that can be fixed later should you change your mind.  I would not let any one tell me I am wrong with the specialization I chose ... unless it was ABJ or DIV ... because the first one you hit has a good chance to being a play-style characteristic of you.  Go with it.  Just don't go with ABJ or DIV for sure.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This is just my opinion, hope it helps ya.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;Hate to rain on your parade but, if you solo via Root/Rot. Conjuration is the way to go.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alteration:&lt;br&gt;Buffs? you do it once. Spend under 2K mana on buffs... that's 220 mana savings&lt;br&gt;Ensanre? 35 mana and you get to save 11% oh.... 4 mana savings... big wow.&lt;br&gt;Root? Clicky pants = Free mana&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Conjuration:&lt;br&gt;Wasp Swarm: 454 Mana&lt;br&gt;Swarming Death: 357 Mana&lt;br&gt;Winged Death: 229 Mana&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;11% of that is about 114 mana saving in a 1 minute. If you use several rounds of DoTs, it will quickly add up. In 3 rounds of DoTs, you would beat out your Alteration mana savings in under 5 minutes, Conjuration beats on on Alteration anyday if Root/Rotting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;And if you ever Root/Rot in Vxed or a 69.1 Hard. You will want your Affliction Efficency, Muram's Anger, Spell Haste Foci, Max FT as well as Conjuration Specialization.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
